      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 3,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"injected_lesson_block\": \"Known failure modes to verify before claiming\\nThese are advisory lessons from previous supervisor runs. They do not satisfy any gate by themselves.\\nUse them as a checklist only: do not block, revise, deny, or accept solely because a lesson exists. A step-repetition lesson applies only when current evidence proves the same handoff, artifacts, and source state are being repeated.\\n1. [missing_worker_signal] worker_invocation (source_run_id=cffe55b8-47b9-4cc0-b025-586aeb0ee5e9): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n2. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\\n3. [FM-1.3] Step repetition (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Change the plan or evidence before retrying; do not repeat the same handoff.\\n4. [FM-1.1] Disobey task specification (source_run_id=40f4ecea-e8bd-4639-aec6-27d686743e8f): Repair the planning artifact or traceability gap before invoking the lead again.\\n5. [FM-1.5] Unaware of termination conditions (source_run_id=f89bc699-1b4e-4713-95b7-d1493a3acfd8): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\",\n  \"injected_lesson_block_sha256\": \"2bb8428cccc8b42b9e1dd42dae45cd87c427ef07c8197b8acf9db9c7f3c8b92a\",\n  \"injected_lesson_ids\": [\n    \"lesson-6e3b08262245b3eade5743e9ddb1a92bfb42a34ec49e8b4f2b0792ca1834a590\",\n    \"lesson-833931ec30fbdcacaef5c7df91fae73a71b7ac537110ccf9cab2ec2e80ec6a52\",\n    \"lesson-cd61385380aa0d71d9927ec5c8f719f315a9191aaf387fdc93862d0a6d71f1ef\",\n    \"lesson-eb78dbaff424a8c1f8dd96b677ccdcb5dd267ca011698619ae37e54156f2eaab\",\n    \"lesson-49755707839e187f3a6fa0e4e84e237398d1457f2fe1421f8f1f53faa6cbbb9e\"\n  ],\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nRun a report-only, code-grounded supervisor-gated audit of all auto-improvement proposals and identify what remains uncompleted, separating implemented mechanisms from live-proven behavior without activating experiments or applying policy.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\\n\\nCorrective context from the previous round:\\nagents have not both accepted yet; revise and continue\\n\\nRuntime TDD test contract:\\nThe supervisor runtime floor will verify that every TDD-named test below appears in supervisor-generated runtime evidence. Include tests/commands covering all of them in outcome.tests. Explicitly skipped tests must carry a recorded pytest skip reason; silently absent tests block the gate.\\nUse only canonical gate decisions (`accept`, `revise`, or `deny`). Do not return `accept_with_residual`; if test execution needs verification, declare the exact pytest commands/nodeids and let the supervisor runtime floor rerun them.\\n- test_planning_artifacts_pass_all_route_gates\\n- test_report_classifies_proposal_completion_from_code\\n- test_report_only_audit_does_not_mutate_policy_or_queue\\n- test_liveness_metrics_are_not_overclaimed\\n- test_terminal_gate_status_is_reported_truthfully\\n\\nKnown failure modes to verify before claiming\\nThese are advisory lessons from previous supervisor runs. They do not satisfy any gate by themselves.\\nUse them as a checklist only: do not block, revise, deny, or accept solely because a lesson exists. A step-repetition lesson applies only when current evidence proves the same handoff, artifacts, and source state are being repeated.\\n1. [missing_worker_signal] worker_invocation (source_run_id=cffe55b8-47b9-4cc0-b025-586aeb0ee5e9): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n2. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\\n3. [FM-1.3] Step repetition (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Change the plan or evidence before retrying; do not repeat the same handoff.\\n4. [FM-1.1] Disobey task specification (source_run_id=40f4ecea-e8bd-4639-aec6-27d686743e8f): Repair the planning artifact or traceability gap before invoking the lead again.\\n5. [FM-1.5] Unaware of termination conditions (source_run_id=f89bc699-1b4e-4713-95b7-d1493a3acfd8): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/proposal-completion-audit-20260614/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"8635d9d9bbc2c7c919da3c1d01167bb1b000fc28a2e76066641d3562946516e5\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n